        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 3:42PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 342 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Moneta, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bedford...
Moneta...
Huddleston...
Forest...
Smith Mountain Lake State Park...
Goode...
and Goodview.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
